<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Daniel Edmund Rochatka, a software architect and product engineer focused on AI systems, platform architecture, data-intensive products, and independent research."
>
  <section class="page-intro section-pad">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>I work between product reality and architectural possibility.</h1>
  </section>
  <section class="about-grid section-pad rule-top">
    <div class="about-lede">
      <p>I am a software architect and product engineer focused on AI systems, platform architecture, data-intensive applications, and 0→1 product development.</p>
      <p>My work moves between practical implementation and deeper system design: shipping software, improving infrastructure, defining product boundaries, and developing frameworks for problems that existing architectures do not handle well.</p>
      <p>I also publish independent research spanning retrieval-augmented generation, foundational physics, and biomedical data. Those works are kept at the <a href="/research/">research record</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="principles">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h2>Build from first principles</h2>
        <p>Question inherited abstractions when they obscure the actual problem.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h2>Preserve operational truth</h2>
        <p>A design is incomplete until deployment, failure, ownership, and change are accounted for.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h2>Keep evidence attached</h2>
        <p>AI and knowledge systems should expose provenance, uncertainty, and disagreement instead of hiding them.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="company-boundary section-pad rule-top">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Separation</p>
      <h2>Daniel Rochatka is the author. Procyonsoft is the company.</h2>
    </div>
    <p>This domain is the durable personal record for my identity, work, research, and writing. Procyonsoft has its own brand, services, infrastructure, and commercial purpose.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
